author: julianfoad
msg: Teach symmetric merge to reject all the scenarios that 'reintegrate'
rejected, when merging in the 'reintegrate' direction.  In particular, it
now rejects the merge if any revision in the common ancestry of the two
branches is not recorded as merged to the source branch.  This makes
merge_symmetric_tests.py 10 pass, because the merge now emits the
expected error about such an unmerged revision.
This implementation is somewhat inefficient in that it duplicates some
mergeinfo fetching and other work that has already been done;
to check for and reject unsupported reintegrate scenarios.
